Ekurhuleni - Motorists were on Monday warned to avoid the N3 highway following an earlier accident that claimed four lives and left 13 people injured. 
This comes after a minibus taxi and BMW SUV collided on the N3 northbound on Monday morning, resulting in a pile-up on the freeway.

Ekurhuleni Emergency Services spokesman William Ntladi confirmed the accident and the closure of one section of the highway as a result.
